					<div class="faq-item">
						<input type="checkbox" id="fq1" class="faq-toggle" />
						<label for="fq1" class="faq-q">What ages is Club FLE for?<span class="faq-chevron"></span></label>
						<div class="faq-a"><p>All ages — from elementary school kids just learning about coins and bills, through teens managing their first paychecks, to college students planning tuition and launching businesses.</p></div>
					</div>

					<div class="faq-item">
						<input type="checkbox" id="fq2" class="faq-toggle" />
						<label for="fq2" class="faq-q">Is it free?<span class="faq-chevron"></span></label>
						<div class="faq-a"><p>The core platform is completely free to start. We believe every kid should have access to financial education regardless of their family's income.</p></div>
					</div>

					<div class="faq-item">
						<input type="checkbox" id="fq3" class="faq-toggle" />
						<label for="fq3" class="faq-q">Can schools use this?<span class="faq-chevron"></span></label>
						<div class="faq-a"><p>Absolutely. Our School branch includes a full standards-aligned classroom curriculum with lesson plans, student activities, and progress tracking — ready to deploy with zero prep time.</p></div>
					</div>

					<div class="faq-item">
						<input type="checkbox" id="fq4" class="faq-toggle" />
						<label for="fq4" class="faq-q">Is real money involved?<span class="faq-chevron"></span></label>
						<div class="faq-a"><p>No real funds are ever at risk. The investing simulator uses practice money so kids can learn market strategies, compound interest, and diversification without any financial exposure.</p></div>
					</div>

					<div class="faq-item">
						<input type="checkbox" id="fq5" class="faq-toggle" />
						<label for="fq5" class="faq-q">How do families use it together?<span class="faq-chevron"></span></label>
						<div class="faq-a"><p>Parents connect their accounts and set up allowance tracking, shared savings goals, and real-time progress monitoring. The family dashboard keeps everyone on the same page.</p></div>
					</div>

				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

